<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!--
Shared URDF properties.

`model_scale` is the single source of truth for uniform length scaling. Edit
the value here when Lucy is measured; no launch/CLI argument is plumbed.

It is referenced as ${model_scale} in robot_description.urdf.xacro on every
joint <origin xyz>, in-link <visual>/<collision> <origin xyz>, and primitive
collision sizes (box/cylinder/sphere). Mesh <mesh scale="..."> is left at
1 1 1 so DAE files are never re-exported.

Default 0.1196 targets a measured crown height of 1.80 m. Earlier values:
0.1163 ≈ 1.75 m, 0.113 ≈ 1.70 m — each bump is the height ratio. Replace
if the measured factor changes.
-->
<robot xmlns:xacro="http://www.ros.org/wiki/xacro">

  <xacro:property name="model_scale" value="0.1196"/>

</robot>
